</taxonomicName>
n. sp. ♂, det.: F. Koch, 2016&quot; [red] (OLML).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">The new species is named after Nigeria, the country in which the holotype was collected.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Nigeria (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 37. Distribution map for Pampsilota leleupi, Pampsilota luederitzensis, Pampsilota nigeriae, Pampsilota tsavoensis, and Pampsilota zebra." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118807" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
adults resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the mostly yellow colour of the abdomen and thorax underside, but differs from both in its predominantly yellow antenna and the bicoloured stigma. The penis valves of 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 15–19" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 15 - 19. Pampsilota dahomeyanus: 15. Valvulae 3 (lateral aspect); 16. Valvulae 3 (dorsal aspect); 17. Lancet; 18. Serrulae 10 - 11; 19. Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures15-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118793" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">19</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 26. Pampsilota nigeriae: Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118798" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">26</figureCitation>
) show differences. Additionally, the dorsal part of mesepisternum is blackish in 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but yellow in 
<taxonomicName authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
